اعتباراً من 17 يونيو، تم تسجيل 81 هدفاً في 40 مباراة بمتوسط 2.03 هدفاً في المباراة الواحدة.





Several Iranian players started their away match against South Korea wearing green armbands or wristbands, a symbol of protest at the outcome of the Iranian presidential election. Most removed them at half-time. The newspaper "Iran" reported that علي كريمي، مهدي مهدفيكيا، Hosein Kaebi, and Vahid Hashemian had received life bans from the Iranian FA for the gesture. However, the Iranian FA denied this claim in a response to FIFA's inquiry saying that "the comments in foreign media are nothing but lies and a mischievous act." The منتخب إيران لكرة القدم head coach Afshin Ghotbi also confirmed that it was a rumour and Iranian FA "has not taken any official stand on this issue."


